            "voted_up": false,
            "votes_up": 1,
            "weighted_score": 0.5,
            "steam_purchase": true,
            "review_text": "same old slop every year, partly because people like me buy it, and mostly because they only cater to online multiplayer chuds that still play this game. I have always hoped that offline modes would be improved but now i just hope they haven't become worse (they have.).\r\n\r\nencountered multiple game breaking bugs, and other bugs that shouldn't exist when it's a company the size of EA - but here we are. if you're someone who only wants to buy it for the offline modes, don't expect too much. it is only fun because it somewhat replicates the feeling of the older fifa games occasionally, at least for me, so i spupose that's one of the only positives. none of the gameplay is \"bad\" per se, but it's just lazy and basically the same thing repeated over 4 iterations of the game. EA had gold on their hands and they somehow turned it into a horrifying and lazy mess, and i will always despise them for it.\r\n\r\nregardless - my goofy ass will still play it because i love and hate it. don't ever buy on full price, and to be honest, don't bother at all."
        },
